[mongo-php-adapter|https://github.com/alcaeus/mongo-php-adapter] uses generators to wrap a {{MongoDB\Driver\Cursor}} and implement the legacy driver's {{MongoCursor}} API:

 * [lib/Mongo/MongoCursor.php|https://github.com/alcaeus/mongo-php-adapter/blob/30ae9000b44ed1ff012dfc9ee5a75b9dd98df1ce/lib/Mongo/MongoCursor.php#L453]
 * [lib/Alcaeus/MongoDbAdapter/AbstractCursor.php|https://github.com/alcaeus/mongo-php-adapter/blob/13580f79f9465daa5781dc2cbe46c97732447762/lib/Alcaeus/MongoDbAdapter/AbstractCursor.php#L292]

On PHP 5.x, this can lead to use-after-free segfaults with {{mongoc_client_t}}. Tracing revealed that {{MongoDB\Driver\Manager}} may still be freed before {{MongoDB\Driver\Cursor}}, which was something previously addressed in PHPC-671; however, that issue did not involve generators.

As with PHPC-671, we should also confirm if a use-after-free crash can be triggered with just a Server object.

